main event: On April 3, 1966, a 9-year-old observer saw two unidentified objects in the sky while using binoculars in Union, New Jersey.
interesting points: The first object was brightly colored with green, yellow, and bright orange colors and was moving at approximately 120 mph., Five minutes later, another object was observed with a bright orange outline and yellow inside., The witness reported the sighting to the local police department., The conclusion of the report was labeled as [CENSORED/UNRELIABLE]., The sighting was timed at 12:25 PM and the observer mentioned that the object traveled noiselessly.
